messages.content: You know the psychological horror video game Mouthwashing by Wrong Organ? What do you know about it?

*Mouthwashing*, a 2024 psychological horror game developed by Wrong Organ, is set on the spaceship Tulpar after a crash leaves the five-person crew stranded in space with dwindling supplies [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0]. The crew blames the captain, Curly, for deliberately crashing the ship [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4].

**Gameplay Mechanics:** The game is played from a first-person perspective [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4] and features non-linear storytelling that jumps between different time periods [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5]. Players explore the ship, interact with characters, and solve fetch quests and light puzzles to advance the narrative [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [thejimquisition](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8] [sixoneindie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6]. Some segments involve stealth or evading creatures [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [sixoneindie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6]. The game uses a low-poly, PS1-inspired aesthetic [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10] [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5], with data moshing used for transitions [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10].

**Psychological Themes:** *Mouthwashing* explores themes of responsibility, guilt, and complicity [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0], human depravity, and failed leadership [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1]. It delves into isolation, mental breakdown [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1], corporate critique [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7], coping mechanisms [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [witherlyheights](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12] [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11], guilt, fears [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10], trauma, and abuse [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5]. The game also touches on moral failure [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1], inner darkness [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13], loss of hope, and descent into madness [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11].

**Development and Influences:** Wrong Organ was founded by Futuregames students [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4), who were inspired by films like *Alien*, *Event Horizon*, and *The Shining* [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6]. The game was developed using the Unity engine [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [igdb](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1]. The developers used a Zoom H1N recorder for most sound effects, aiming for a late 90s/early 2000s horror feel [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3) [analogstickgaming](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4].

*Mouthwashing* has been praised for its narrative, visual style, and thought-provoking experience [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4], earning a cult following and a Game of the Year nomination at the 2024 Indie Game Awards [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9].

Okay, I will conduct Google Searches to gather the most recent information on "Mouthwashing Wrong Organ gameplay mechanics and psychological themes" and synthesize it into a verifiable text artifact.
"Mouthwashing," a 2024 psychological horror game developed by Wrong Organ, explores dark themes and complex characters within a narrative set on the spaceship Tulpar [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2). The game takes place in a non-specific future and follows the five-person crew of the Tulpar after a crash leaves them stranded in space with dwindling supplies [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). The crew blames the captain, Curly, who is alive but severely maimed and unable to communicate, for deliberately crashing the ship [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).

**Gameplay Mechanics:**

*   **First-Person Perspective:** The game is played from a first-person perspective [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **Non-Linear Storytelling:** The narrative jumps between different time periods, mirroring the fractured mental states of the characters [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   **Exploration and Dialogue:** Gameplay involves wandering the ship, interacting with characters, and discovering more about them and the events leading to the crash [sixoneindie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).
*   **Fetch Quests and Puzzles:** The gameplay includes fetch quests and light puzzle-solving, which serve to move the narrative forward [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [thegamingbrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [thejimquisition](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).
*   **Stealth and Evasion:** Some segments involve stealth or evading creatures [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [sixoneindie](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).
*   **Visual Style:** The game uses a low-poly, PS1-inspired aesthetic, creating an atmosphere of nostalgia and unease [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9) [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). Data moshing, a trippy visual effect, is used to transition between areas [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10).

**Psychological Themes:**

*   **Responsibility and Complicity:** The game grapples with questions of responsibility, guilt, and complicity, highlighting how silence and willful ignorance can enable abuse [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). The phrase "take responsibility" appears throughout the game [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Human Depravity and Failed Leadership:** "Mouthwashing" questions the depths of human depravity and the consequences of failed leadership [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   **Isolation and Mental Breakdown:** The confined space of the ship becomes a metaphor for the limitations of the mind when faced with extreme stress and isolation [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). The game explores the darkest recesses of the human psyche and the capacity for violence that lurks within seemingly ordinary people [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   **Corporate Critique:** Beyond the character-driven horror, the game offers a scathing critique of corporate culture and capitalist excess [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). The premise of transporting mouthwash across space is a commentary on the absurdities of capitalist pursuits [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). The ship design reflects the company's interests over the crew's well-being [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7).
*   **Coping Mechanisms:** The game touches on themes of fulfillment, relationships, and madness, all shaped by the characters' coping mechanisms [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11). Characters turn to different methods of coping, such as Anya trying to preserve Curly, Swansea resorting to alcoholism, and Jimmy attempting to "fix" everything [witherlyheights](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11).
*   **Guilt and Fears:** The game delves into frightening nightmare scenarios based on the protagonist's guilt and fears [gameinformer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10).
*   **Trauma and Abuse:** The game hints at heavy themes, including sexual assault and mental breakdown [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). It reveals that Jimmy has raped and impregnated a coworker, Anya, before stranding his crew [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). The game delivers this reveal through piecemeal anecdotes, allowing the player to come to that realization on their own [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   **Moral Failure:** The game aims to make players question their own capacity for moral failure and the blurry line between complicity and culpability [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   **Inner Darkness:** The game explores the inner darkness of people, with each character representing aspects of ourselves [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).
*   **Loss of Hope and Descent into Madness:** The game portrays the chilling experience of losing hope and descending into madness [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11).

"Mouthwashing" is praised for its narrative, visual style, and ability to create a disturbing and thought-provoking experience [somanygames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [georgetowngazette](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). It has garnered a cult following and has been nominated for Game of the Year at the 2024 Indie Game Awards [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9).
Wrong Organ, a Stockholm-based game developer, created the horror game *Mouthwashing* [wrongorgan](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0). The studio was founded by a group of students from Futuregames, a game development trade school in Sweden [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). The founders, who met in the Game Design class of 2021, include Kai Moore, Jeffrey Tomec, and Johanna Kasurinen [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).

**Origins and Influences:**

*   **Futuregames:** Wrong Organ's origins lie in a shared creative vision developed during their time at Futuregames [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1). According to Kai Moore, the success of *How Fish is Made*, a school project, motivated them to form Wrong Organ [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Narrative and Themes:** *Mouthwashing* is a narrative-driven psychological horror game set on a spaceship called the Tulpar [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). The game explores themes of isolation, confinement, and the deterioration of people in dire circumstances [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3). Johanna Kasurinen described the game as "Twin Peaks in space," emphasizing its psychological horror elements [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2).
*   **Inspirations:** The developers drew inspiration from various films, including *Alien*, *Event Horizon*, *Sunshine*, *The Thing*, *The Shining*, and *Pandorum* [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6). *The Lighthouse* was also an influence, particularly in depicting a small, confined space and descent into madness [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). *Iron Lung* inspired the confined space of the game [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Low-Poly Aesthetic:** *Mouthwashing* employs a low-poly, retro visual style inspired by PlayStation games [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). The developers felt this aesthetic added an uneasy vibe and allowed players to use their imagination to fill in the gaps [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). Johanna Kasurinen noted that nostalgia for games like *Spyro the Dragon* and *Silent Hill* also played a role in this artistic choice [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). The hand-painted textures aimed to evoke "if Crash Bandicoot went to Silent Hill" [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**Design and Development:**

*   **Non-Linearity:** The game features a split, non-linear narrative, with disjointed scenes taking place before and after the crash [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **The Tulpar:** The design of the Tulpar was crucial to the game's atmosphere. The developers wanted it to feel confusing and maze-like, creating anxiety for the player [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3). The ship's interior features contrasting industrial hallways and eccentric crew quarters, both designed to be oppressive [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Audio:** Audio design was a key element in maintaining pacing and creating a disturbing atmosphere [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Characters:** The characters' visual designs are loosely based on popular horror media characters [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5). For example, Anya was inspired by Shelley Duvall's Wendy from *The Shining*, and Daisuke's look is based on Ryosuke Kawashima from the film *Kairo* [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Mouthwash:** The choice of mouthwash as the ship's cargo was intended to add a humorous element to the situation's sadness [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

**Company Philosophy:**

*   **Weird Games:** Wrong Organ aims to create "weird games" that resonate with their audience [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). They prioritize their creative vision and focus on telling stories they feel need telling, even if they are strange or non-commercial [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Future Plans:** While they want to stick to an 18-month development cycle, Wrong Organ doesn't want to be pigeonholed as a "walking sim company" [skyboxcritics](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). They aim to showcase their ability to create strong gameplay-driven experiences in the future [futuregames](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Team Dynamic:** The developers describe their office environment as light-hearted and jovial, contrasting with the dark themes of their games [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).

Wrong Organ utilized the Unity game engine to develop "Mouthwashing" [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [igdb](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). The game employs a low-poly, retro visual style reminiscent of original PlayStation titles [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).

Here's how the tools contributed to the game's unique visual style and atmosphere:

*   **Unity Engine:** The choice of Unity as the game engine provided a foundation for the developers to create the game and bring their artistic vision to life [igdb](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1).
*   **Low-Poly Graphics:** The deliberate use of early 2000s polygon art and textures isn't just a way to cut corners [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). It's a deliberate aesthetic choice that amplifies the hopeless and desolate atmosphere, making the grim situation more palatable [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). The low-poly graphics were labeled as "beautiful" by one reviewer, while another stated that they "invite us to imagine the finer details for ourselves" [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). The low poly horror stylings also hide a triple A art direction [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Audio Design:** The audio design was split into two main areas: the ambience present in any given scene (SFX and music), and keeping the pacing of the game as a whole feeling good [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). The developers recorded almost all sounds using the Zoom H1N recorder, except for larger-than-life effects like explosions, which were mixed using sound libraries and synthesized sounds [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3) [analogstickgaming](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4). To achieve the late 90's and early 2000's horror game feel, they used sound libraries popular at the time to honor their inspirations [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). Throughout the game (except for very few silent scenes) there's an audible cassette tape hum and noise floor underlying every chapter to make the environment feel gritty and grimy, and helps blend the sounds in the game together [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). A dynamic ambience system was put into place, adapting to the timeline of the game, how broken the ship is and what systems still function, enhancing the atmosphere of the ship and notifying the player what part of the timeline you're currently playing [steamcommunity](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3).
*   **Visual Inspiration:** The developers drew inspiration from films like *Alien*, *Event Horizon*, *Sunshine*, *The Thing*, *The Shining*, and *Pandorum* [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). The game's visuals are reminiscent of the pixelated, dark, and moody world of *Silent Hill* [analogstickgaming](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4). The interior is futuristic, but at the same time retro, somewhere in between atompunk and the dirty, worn aesthetics of the *Alien* franchise with its kitschy 70s-style furniture and clunky technology [gameluster](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5).
*   **Narrative Structure:** The game employs a split, nonlinear narrative, playing out across disjointed scenes taking place in the weeks and months before and following the crash [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). The player jumps between scenes before and after the accident and occasionally takes the vantage of some of the other characters, navigating through hallucinations or dreams [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2).
